.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md-74-- Legacy observation through the existing frozen `router-replay.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md-75-- Route-gold checks for both normalized observations through the existing frozen `evaluateRouteGold()` export.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md-76-- A routing-only equality projection: action, selection kind, ordered workflow/surface targets, and defer/reject outcome. Policy hashes, generations, timing, and additive metadata do not participate in routing equality.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:77:- A default-on parity gate for hubs whose shared eligibility predicate reports a valid fresh manifest; no-manifest hubs are recorded as legacy by construction rather than treated as a compiled failure.
