A first split is emerging: compiled serving does not create seven new routing semantics; it creates one activation/authority layer over several existing router outcome shapes. I’m now collapsing the seven hubs into equivalence classes so the spec adds only cases that prove a distinct branch—single route, ordered bundle/surface bundle, defer/clarify, and fallback/kill-switch—without cloning every legacy scenario.
