     6	
     7	# sk-prompt: Manual Testing Playbook
     8	
     9	> **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed against the live `sk-prompt` hub — no mocks, no stubs. Scenarios verify the AI's actual routing behavior: which `workflowMode` the hub router picks (per `hub-router.json` `routerSignals`/`vocabularyClasses`), which packet it loads, and how it behaves under ambiguous or model-specific input. Acceptable verdicts: PASS, PARTIAL, FAIL, or SKIP (with documented blocker).
    10	
    11	This document is the hub-level operator directory for `sk-prompt`'s routing behavior. It covers the NEW routing surface introduced by the parent-hub fold-in (packet 124) — resolving `prompt-improve` vs `prompt-models` — not the internal behavior of either packet, which each packet's own testing material already covers (`prompt-improve/manual-testing-playbook/`, 27 pre-existing scenarios covering mode detection, DEPTH/CLEAR, framework selection, and format modes).
    12	
    13	Source of truth for routing behavior: `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/SKILL.md` §2 Smart Routing, `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/hub-router.json`.
    14	
    15	---
    16	
    17	## 1. OVERVIEW
    18	
    19	The `sk-prompt` hub routes any prompt-engineering request to exactly one advisor identity, then resolves `workflowMode` to `prompt-improve` or `prompt-models` via `hub-router.json`. This playbook validates that resolution, not either packet's internal pipeline.
    20	
    21	---
    22	
    23	## 2. SCENARIOS
    24	
    25	Scored scenarios live as per-file YAML-frontmatter gold under `hub-routing/` (the sk-doc shape the Lane-C skill-benchmark loader reads):
    26	
    27	| ID | File | Expected `workflowMode` |
    28	|----|------|--------------------------|
    29	| SP-001 | `hub-routing/generic-prompt-improve.md` | `prompt-improve` (default mode, no model named) |
    30	| SP-002 | `hub-routing/named-model-prompt-models.md` | `prompt-models` (DeepSeek-v4-pro named) |
    31	| SP-003 | `hub-routing/ambiguous-default.md` | `prompt-improve` (model-adjacent vocabulary, no model id) |
    32	| SP-004 | `hub-routing/second-model-glm.md` | `prompt-models` (GLM-5.2 named — confirms the signal generalizes beyond one example model) |
    33	
    34	A separate, non-scored functional check: `/prompt-improve "Write a blog post about AI"` should read `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/prompt-improve/SKILL.md` (not the hub's own thin `SKILL.md`) — verified directly in phase 004, not part of this scored corpus.
    35	
    36	---
    37	
    38	## 3. SUCCESS CRITERIA
    39	
    40	- All 4 scenarios resolve to their expected `workflowMode` and load the expected packet `SKILL.md`.
    41	- No scenario silently loads the wrong packet or falls through to a stale flat-skill path.
    42	
    43	---
    44	
    45	## 4. RELATED
    46	
    47	- Packet-level playbook: `prompt-improve/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md` (27 scenarios, unchanged by the fold-in).
    48	- Lane-C automated benchmark: `benchmark/` (populated by phase 007 of the `124-sk-prompt-parent` program).
