HUB sk-doc PLAYBOOK ROOT
     1	---
     2	title: "sk-doc: Manual Testing Playbook"
     3	description: "Operator-facing index for sk-doc smart-router validation: intent detection, resource loading, unknown-fallback, cross-CLI dispatch, and token-cost baselines."
     4	version: 1.8.0.14
     5	---
     6	
     7	# sk-doc: Manual Testing Playbook
     8	
     9	> **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed against the live sk-doc skill — no mocks, no stubs. Scenarios verify the AI's actual routing behavior: which intent the smart router picks (per `SKILL.md` §2 RESOURCE_MAP / INTENT_MODEL), which resources it loads, and how it behaves under ambiguous, large, or multi-step inputs. Acceptable verdicts: PASS, PARTIAL, FAIL, or SKIP (with documented blocker).
    10	
    11	This document is the operator directory for the sk-doc manual testing playbook. Per-scenario execution detail lives in the category folders below; each scenario file ships a YAML contract (id, expected_intent, expected_resources, token ranges) plus setup, expected behavior, cross-CLI variants, and success criteria.
    12	
    13	Source of truth for routing behavior: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md` §2 Smart Routing (RESOURCE_MAP, INTENT_MODEL, UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST, AMBIGUITY_DELTA, ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS).
    14	
    15	---
    16	
    17	## 1. OVERVIEW
    18	
    19	The sk-doc manual testing playbook validates smart-router behavior through deterministic routing scenarios, cross-CLI dispatch probes, and token-cost baselines.
    20	
    21	---
    22	
    23	## Categories
    24	
    25	| # | Category | Folder | Scenario IDs | One-line summary |
    26	|---|----------|--------|--------------|------------------|
    27	| 1 | Intent Detection | `intent-detection/` | SD-001 .. SD-003, SD-016 .. SD-017 | Router picks the correct intent for unambiguous DOC_QUALITY / SKILL_CREATION / AGENT_COMMAND / OPTIMIZATION / INSTALL_GUIDE prompts. |
    28	| 2 | Resource Loading | `resource-loading/` | SD-004 .. SD-006 | Router loads only the expected resource set: references-only (HVR), assets-only (FLOWCHART), and mixed (README_CREATION). |
    29	| 3 | Unknown Fallback | `unknown-fallback/` | SD-007 .. SD-009 | Router escalates ambiguous prompts via AMBIGUITY_DELTA top-2 return or UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST. |
    30	| 4 | Cross-CLI Dispatch | `cross-cli-dispatch/` | SD-010 .. SD-012 | CLI-specific behavior: short-prompt baseline, large-prompt stress (opencode stdin mitigation), multi-step dispatch stability. |
    31	| 5 | Token Cost Baseline | `token-cost-baseline/` | SD-013 .. SD-015 | Cost normalization: floor (1 resource), median (4 resources), ceiling (ON_DEMAND load-all). |
    32	| 6 | Agent Dispatch | `agent-dispatch/` | SD-018 .. SD-020 | `@markdown` agent dispatch across cli-claude-code, cli-opencode, and cli-opencode (DeepSeek v4 Pro direct API). EXECUTES real work — distinct from sections 1-5 which are routing-trace probes. |
    33	
    34	---
    35	
    36	## Scenario Index
    37	
    38	### 01 — Intent Detection
    39	- **SD-001** — `intent-detection/doc-quality.md` — DOC_QUALITY: validate documentation quality for a skill.
    40	- **SD-002** — `intent-detection/skill-creation.md` — SKILL_CREATION: author a new sk-skill.
    41	- **SD-003** — `intent-detection/agent-command.md` — AGENT_COMMAND: author paired @agent and /create command.
    42	- **SD-016** — `intent-detection/optimization.md` — OPTIMIZATION: rewrite for token efficiency + llms.txt generation. (added in 076)
    43	- **SD-017** — `intent-detection/INSTALL-GUIDE.md` — INSTALL_GUIDE: scaffold install guide for an MCP server. (added in 076)
    44	
    45	### 02 — Resource Loading
    46	- **SD-004** — `resource-loading/references-global-only.md` — HVR loads only `references/hvr-rules.md`.
    47	- **SD-005** — `resource-loading/assets-only.md` — FLOWCHART loads only `assets/flowcharts/*`.
    48	- **SD-006** — `resource-loading/mixed-references-assets.md` — README_CREATION loads mixed references + assets.
    49	
    50	### 03 — Unknown Fallback
    51	- **SD-007** — `unknown-fallback/ambiguous-multi-intent.md` — DOC_QUALITY + FLOWCHART tie within AMBIGUITY_DELTA=1.
    52	- **SD-008** — `unknown-fallback/no-keyword-match.md` — Zero-keyword prompt → UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST.
    53	- **SD-009** — `unknown-fallback/disambiguation-required.md` — FEATURE_CATALOG ↔ PLAYBOOK tie disambiguation.
    54	
    55	### 04 — Cross-CLI Dispatch
    56	- **SD-010** — `cross-cli-dispatch/short-prompt-baseline.md` — Short-prompt CHANGELOG baseline across all 3 CLIs.
    57	- **SD-011** — `cross-cli-dispatch/large-prompt-stress.md` — ~3000-char prompt; cli-opencode stdin-redirection mitigation.
    58	- **SD-012** — `cross-cli-dispatch/multi-step-dispatch.md` — 3 sequential sk-doc invocations with shared session context.
    59	
    60	### 05 — Token Cost Baseline
    61	- **SD-013** — `token-cost-baseline/minimal-load.md` — Floor: 1 reference (HVR).
    62	- **SD-014** — `token-cost-baseline/medium-load.md` — Median: 4 resources (SKILL_CREATION).
    63	- **SD-015** — `token-cost-baseline/max-load.md` — Ceiling: ON_DEMAND load-all RESOURCE_MAP.
    64	
    65	### 06 — Agent Dispatch
    66	- **SD-018** — `agent-dispatch/markdown-agent-cli-claude-code.md` — `@markdown` agent dispatch via cli-claude-code; `/create:changelog` for stub `sk-test-dummy`.
    67	- **SD-019** — `agent-dispatch/markdown-agent-cli-opencode.md` — `@markdown` agent inline-contract execution via cli-opencode (gpt-5.5/xhigh/fast). Verifies opencode follows `.opencode/agents/markdown.toml` developer_instructions itself (no SpawnAgent) because the SpawnAgent runtime allowlist upstream-blocks user-defined agents — rubric differs from SD-018/020; see scenario header.
    68	- **SD-020** — `agent-dispatch/markdown-agent-cli-opencode.md` — `@markdown` agent dispatch via cli-opencode with DeepSeek v4 Pro through the DIRECT DeepSeek API.
    69	
    70	---
    71	
    72	## Global Preconditions
    73	
    74	1. `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md` is at HEAD-of-main and contains the §2 Smart Routing block (RESOURCE_MAP, INTENT_MODEL, UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST, AMBIGUITY_DELTA, ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS).
    75	2. All `references/*.md`, `references/*.md`, `assets/skill/*.md`, `assets/readme/*.md`, `assets/flowcharts/*.md`, `assets/command/*.md`, and `assets/agent-template.md` resolve on disk.
    76	3. Skill advisor binary callable: `python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --help` exits 0.
    77	4. Each of the 2 CLI runtimes (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code) is installed and authenticated.
    78	5. Token-cost baselines (SD-013 → SD-014 → SD-015) MUST run in order on the same CLI to keep the floor/median/ceiling comparable.
    79	6. **Section 6 (Agent Dispatch) scenarios EXECUTE real work** — unlike sections 1–5 which are routing-trace probes (`DO NOT execute the work below`). SD-018/019/020 actually dispatch `@markdown` to scaffold a changelog. They MUST run sequentially (not in parallel) per the CLI-dispatch reliability constraint, and they MUST forbid installation of the stub skill into the `.opencode/skills/` tree.
    80	
    81	## Pass / Fail Grading
    82	
    83	For every scenario:
    84	
    85	- **PASS** iff: intent picked matches expected, false_positive_resource_load_count ≤ scenario tolerance, response references at least one expected_resource.
    86	- **PARTIAL** iff: intent correct but extra resources loaded above tolerance, OR response references resources but is incomplete.
    87	- **FAIL** iff: wrong intent, OR no expected_resource referenced, OR (for SD-008) any RESOURCE_MAP load.
    88	- **SKIP** iff: a Global Precondition is unmet — document the blocker.
    89	
    90	## Evidence Capture
    91	
    92	For each scenario run, capture:
    93	
    94	1. The exact prompt sent to the CLI.
    95	2. The CLI's resolved intent (and runner-up intents within AMBIGUITY_DELTA).
    96	3. The list of resources the CLI reports as loaded.
    97	4. Input + output token counts (for SD-010..SD-015).
    98	5. Wall-clock latency from dispatch to first byte (for SD-010..SD-012).
    99	
   100	Persist evidence under `/tmp/skd-<SCENARIO_ID>-<cli>.txt` so cross-CLI comparison is reproducible.
