.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-40-- Automated tests cover internals but not operator-visible behavior.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-41-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-42-### When NOT to Use
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-47-- The feature is one-off or experimental.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-48-- The system has only a few manually testable behaviors.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-49-- Automated tests already cover the only meaningful acceptance criteria.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:50:- The user asks for a feature catalog rather than executable validation scenarios. Use `create-feature-catalog`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-51-- The user asks for a README, install guide, skill, agent, command, benchmark package, flowchart, or changelog. Use `create-readme`, `create-skill`, `create-agent`, `create-command`, `create-benchmark`, `create-flowchart`, or `create-changelog`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-52-- The task audits, validates, scores, or optimizes an existing playbook without creating or extending the package. Use `create-quality-control`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-53-
--
