   371	
   372	# {FEATURE_ID} -- {FEATURE_NAME}
   373	
   374	This document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors, and metadata for `{FEATURE_ID}`.
   375	
   376	---
   377	
   378	## 1. OVERVIEW
   379	
   380	This scenario validates {FEATURE_NAME} for `{FEATURE_ID}`. It focuses on {OBJECTIVE}.
   381	
   382	### Why This Matters
   383	
   384	{WHY_THIS_MATTERS}
   385	
   386	---
   387	
   388	## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT
   389	
   390	Operators run the exact prompt and command sequence for `{FEATURE_ID}` and confirm the expected signals without contradictory evidence.
   391	
   392	- Objective: {OBJECTIVE}
   393	- Real user request: `{REAL_USER_REQUEST}`
   394	- Prompt: `{PROMPT — natural-human by default; use RCAF "As a {ROLE}, ..." only when actor is an AI orchestrator. See references/prompt-voice.md.}`
   395	- Expected execution process: {EXPECTED_PROCESS}
   396	- Expected signals: {EXPECTED_SIGNALS}
   397	- Desired user-visible outcome: {DESIRED_USER_OUTCOME}
   398	- Pass/fail: PASS if {PASS_CONDITION}; FAIL if {FAIL_CONDITION}
   399	
   400	---
   401	
   402	## 3. TEST EXECUTION
   403	
   404	### Recommended Orchestration Process
   405	
   406	1. Restate the user request in plain user language.
   407	2. Decide whether the scenario should stay local, delegate to sub-agents, or invoke another CLI/runtime.
   408	3. Execute the deterministic steps exactly as written.
   409	4. Compare the observed output against the desired user-visible outcome.
   410	5. Return a concise final answer that a real user would understand.
   411	
   412	| Feature ID | Feature Name | Scenario Name / Objective | Exact Prompt | Exact Command Sequence | Expected Signals | Evidence | Pass/Fail Criteria | Failure Triage |
   413	|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
   414	| {FEATURE_ID} | {FEATURE_NAME} | Verify {OBJECTIVE} | `{EXACT_PROMPT}` | 1. `{COMMAND_1}` -> 2. `{COMMAND_2}` | Step 1: {SIGNAL_1}; Step 2: {SIGNAL_2} | {EVIDENCE_DESCRIPTION} | PASS if {PASS_CONDITION}; FAIL if {FAIL_CONDITION} | {TRIAGE_STEPS} |
